{"abstract":[{"text":"With iOS 5, you can customize the look of your app controls using the new Appearance APIs. The new Appearance Proxy API allows you to efficiently apply a custom appearance to your views and controls, including built-in controls such navigation, tab, and toolbars. These customizations can be applied across your entire app or independently on a per-control basis.","type":"text"}],"kind":"article","variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/wwdc11-114-customizing-the-appearance-of-uikit-controls"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"metadata":{"title":"Customizing the Appearance of UIKit Controls","modules":[{"name":"WWDC Notes"}],"role":"sampleCode","roleHeading":"WWDC11"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes","doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11"]]},"sections":[],"primaryContentSections":[{"content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"overview","level":2},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"😱 “No Overview Available!”","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Be the hero to change that by watching the video or reading the transcript on WWDCIndex and providing notes! It’s super easy:","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"https:\/\/wwdcnotes.com\/documentation\/wwdcnotes\/contributing"}]}],"kind":"content"}],"identifier":{"interfaceLanguage":"swift","url":"doc:\/\/WWDCNotes\/documentation\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11-114-Customizing-the-Appearance-of-UIKit-Controls"},"sampleCodeDownload":{"action":{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"overridingTitle":"Open on WWDCIndex","identifier":"https:\/\/nonstrict.eu\/wwdcindex\/wwdc2011\/114\/"},"kind":"sampleDownload"},"references":{"WWDC11.jpeg":{"type":"image","alt":null,"identifier":"WWDC11.jpeg","variants":[{"traits":["1x","light"],"url":"\/images\/WWDCNotes\/WWDC11.jpeg"}]},"https://wwdcnotes.com/documentati